✅ Practical 1: Import Data from Different Sources (ETL – Extraction & Loading)
🎯 Aim (simple)

Import data from sources like Excel / SQL / APIs and load it into Power BI.

🛠️ What you need
Power BI Desktop installed
Sample dataset (Excel file like Products.xlsx)
🔹 Step-by-Step Procedure
Part A: Import Excel Data
Open Power BI Desktop
Click Home → Get Data → Excel
Select your Excel file (Products.xlsx)
Click Open
In Navigator:
Select table (e.g., Products)
Click Edit (to open Power Query)
In Power Query:
Check data (optional cleaning)
Click Close & Load

✅ Data is now loaded into Power BI

Part B: Import Data from Online Source (OData Feed)
Go to Home → Get Data → OData Feed

Paste this URL:

http://services.odata.org/V3/Northwind/Northwind.svc/
Click OK
In Navigator:
Select Orders table
Click Edit
Load data:
Click Close & Load
🧠 What you actually did
Extracted data (Excel + API)
Loaded into Power BI
👉 This is ETL (Extraction + Loading)
💡 Viva Points
Data sources: Excel, SQL Server, APIs
Data integrity: validation, cleaning
Handling large data: batching, indexing

✅ Practical 2 and 3: Data Visualization using ETL Process
🎯 Aim

Create dashboards & visuals from the data loaded in Practical 1.

🔹 Step-by-Step Procedure
Step 1: Create Chart – Units in Stock by Product
Go to Report View
From Fields:
Drag UnitsInStock → Canvas
Drag ProductName → Axis
Change visualization:
Select Bar Chart
Sort:
Click 3 dots → Sort by UnitsInStock
Step 2: Create Line Chart – Sales by Year
Drag:
OrderDate → Axis
LineTotal → Values
Change visualization to:
Line Chart
Step 3: Create Map Visualization
Drag:
ShipCountry → Canvas
Power BI auto creates Map
Drag:
LineTotal → Values

👉 Bubble size shows sales per country

Step 4: Interaction (Important for Viva)
Click any country (e.g., Canada)
Observe:
Other charts automatically filter

👉 This is called cross-filtering

🧠 What you actually did
Used ETL processed data
Created:
Bar chart
Line chart
Map
Built an interactive dashboard
💡 Viva Points
🔹 What is ETL?
Extract → Get data
Transform → Clean/process
Load → Store/use
🔹 Why ETL helps visualization?
Clean data = better charts
Structured data = faster analysis
🔹 ETL vs ELT
ETL → Transform before loading
ELT → Transform after loading
🧾 Final Output (What to show in lab)
Loaded dataset
3 visuals:
Product stock chart
Sales line chart
Country map
Interactive dashboard

✅ Practical 4: Data Analysis and Visualization using Advanced Excel
🎯 Aim (write this)

To perform data analysis and create visualizations using advanced Excel features.

🛠️ What you need
Microsoft Excel (2013 or above)
Dataset (use the file I gave: practical4_sales_large.xlsx)
🔹 Step-by-Step Procedure (Lab Execution)
✅ Step 1: Open Dataset
Open Excel
Click File → Open
Load your dataset (practical4_sales_large.xlsx)
✅ Step 2: Convert Data into Table
Select all data
Press Ctrl + T
Click OK

👉 This makes filtering & analysis easier

✅ Step 3: Create Pivot Table (MOST IMPORTANT STEP)
Select data
Go to Insert → PivotTable
Click OK
📊 Create Analysis 1: Sales by Region
Drag:
Region → Rows
Sales → Values

👉 Output: Total sales per region

📊 Create Analysis 2: Profit by Product
Drag:
Product → Rows
Profit → Values
📊 Create Analysis 3: Sales by Year
Drag:
Year → Rows
Sales → Values
✅ Step 4: Create Charts (Visualization)
🔹 Chart 1: Bar Chart
Select Pivot Table (Region vs Sales)
Go to Insert → Bar Chart
🔹 Chart 2: Line Chart (Trend)
Select Year vs Sales
Insert → Line Chart
🔹 Chart 3: Pie Chart (Product Distribution)
Select Product vs Profit
Insert → Pie Chart
✅ Step 5: Apply Filters (Advanced Feature)
Click Pivot Table
Drag:
Region → Filters

👉 Now you can filter data dynamically

✅ Step 6: Use Slicers (VERY IMPRESSIVE IN VIVA)
Click Pivot Table
Go to Insert → Slicer
Select:
Region
Product

👉 This creates clickable filters (looks professional)

✅ Step 7: Conditional Formatting (Optional but adds marks)
Select Sales column
Go to:
Home → Conditional Formatting → Color Scale

👉 Highlights high/low values

📊 Final Output (What examiner expects)
Pivot Tables
3 Charts:
Bar chart
Line chart
Pie chart
Filters / Slicers
